  "texts": [
    "This is because GiBy correctly detected all anomalies outside its normal (seen) trained bounds.",
    "Anomaly Detection Woes: Improving detection accuracy by using alternate definitions and experimentsIn this section we highlight certain techniques used to increase detection accuracy by changing the definition for accuracy seen in Equation (8).",
    "We also discuss serious implications from inflated reporting of detection accuracy and how it affects the works that define and report accuracy in the conventional manner; especially when they are expected to be compared with \"state of the art\" work claiming high accuracies in the 95-99.99% range.",
    "The purpose of this discussion is to highlight the different definitions for the seemingly same reference to the word \"detection accuracy\", and why some works in existing literature are not comparable with GiBy's detection accuracy.",
    "The interpretation of what accuracy measures and how it is reported is inconsistently defined and calculated; making GiBy detection accuracy comparisons incompatible with some works in existing literature."
  ]
